249
00:18:46,170 --> 00:18:58,496
So the statement says on December, excuse me, on Wednesday, January 4th, Cambridge police shot and killed Saeed Faisal, a 20-year-old college student and the only child of Bangladeshi immigrants.

250
00:18:59,196 --> 00:19:11,803
While the investigation is ongoing, it appears that Saeed was in the midst of a mental health crisis and the effort to stop self-harm ended in Saeed being fatally shot by the police.

251
00:19:12,768 --> 00:19:20,572
The Medford Human Rights Commission would like to express its deepest condolences to Sayeed Faisal's family, friends, and community.

252
00:19:21,352 --> 00:19:29,336
We stand with other mental health and minority advocates in finding outcomes like these unacceptable.

253
00:19:30,177 --> 00:19:40,202
Despite police being trained in de-escalation techniques, less than lethal weapons and tactics meant to prevent the need

254
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:53,329
for shootings, mental health crises, and a disproportionate number of incidents involving BIPOC individuals still result in fatal police shootings.

255
00:19:54,290 --> 00:20:02,072
Corrective steps must be taken to ensure that this does not happen again in Cambridge, Medford, or any other community.

256
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:15,299
Local authorities need to invest in the proper training and resources to address mental health crises, including dedicated unarmed experts to help deal with such incidents.

257
00:20:16,099 --> 00:20:21,823
We must not relegate Said to an incident, report, or a statistic.

258
00:20:22,464 --> 00:20:28,748
It is important to remember that Said Faisal was an individual with a life and a story.

259
00:20:29,543 --> 00:20:37,047
We should all work to ensure that mental health crisis episodes do not end in fatal police shootings.

260
00:20:38,308 --> 00:20:40,770
And at the end, there's just a list of ways you can help.

261
00:20:42,411 --> 00:20:47,594
So I'll open this to comments and whatnot.

262
00:20:49,495 --> 00:20:52,657
